Serena Williams Reaches U.S. Open Semifinals With Straight-Set Victory

-- B y   M a s o n   L e v i n s o n
-- 
2011-09-08T18:52:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/serena-williams-reaches-u-s-open-semifinals-with-straight-set-victory.html
Serena Williams  reached the women’s
semifinals at the U.S. Open with a straight-set victory over
17th-seeded Anastasia Pavlyuchenkova of  Russia .  Williams, a three-time champion of the Grand Slam
tournament from the U.S. who is seeded 28th this year, won 7-5,
6-1 at the National Tennis Center in  New York .  Williams hasn’t dropped a set so far in this year’s
championship.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  